00:36:12,793 --> 00:36:15,192
One question's haunted me.

318
00:36:16,513 --> 00:36:17,112
Yes?

319
00:36:17,592 --> 00:36:20,192
Why are there five coins
hanging down here?

320
00:36:21,033 --> 00:36:22,033
Five Emperor Coins.

321
00:36:22,833 --> 00:36:23,833
Round and square.

322
00:36:24,592 --> 00:36:25,592
Cosmic unity.

323
00:36:25,993 --> 00:36:27,072
They ward off evil.

324
00:36:29,232 --> 00:36:29,873
What?

325
00:36:30,793 --> 00:36:31,793
Do you think

326
00:36:33,033 --> 00:36:34,793
I've ruined the integrity
of your artwork?

327
00:36:36,232 --> 00:36:37,473
Not exactly 'ruined.'

328
00:36:38,353 --> 00:36:39,873
Hermit Duck was my early creation.

329
00:36:40,152 --> 00:36:41,513
It accidentally turned out well.

330
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:44,072
No systematic creative philosophy
is behind it.

331
00:36:45,152 --> 00:36:46,953
I just feel they don't match well.

332
00:36:53,953 --> 00:36:54,752
A hermit

333
00:36:55,473 --> 00:36:56,752
retreats from worldly affairs,

334
00:36:57,953 --> 00:37:00,152
free from fame and wealth
and content with simplicity.

335
00:37:02,433 --> 00:37:05,913
Ducks sense the warmth
of spring rivers first.

336
00:37:06,793 --> 00:37:09,232
It's an image full of spring vitality,
warm and cozy.

337
00:37:10,793 --> 00:37:11,712
Five Emperor Coins

338
00:37:12,953 --> 00:37:15,632
attract fortune, wealth, peace, and joy.

339
00:37:17,913 --> 00:37:20,112
Hermit, duck, and coins.

340
00:37:20,552 --> 00:37:23,353
These three elements
complement each other.

341
00:37:23,833 --> 00:37:24,993
A perfect combination.

342
00:37:26,552 --> 00:37:28,513
You're pretending
to be knowledgeable again.

343
00:37:31,953 --> 00:37:34,552
I told you, you're an optimistic person.

344
00:37:37,712 --> 00:37:39,072
Since when does the heir

345
00:37:39,552 --> 00:37:41,272
